SIMPLE: incomparable
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Incomparable
<hw>In*com"pa*ra*ble</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>incomparabilis</ets>: cf. F. <ets>incomparable</ets>. See
<er>In-</er> not, and <er>Comparable</er>.]</ety> <def>Not comparable;
admitting of no comparison with others; unapproachably eminent; without
a peer or equal; matchless; peerless; transcendent.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>A merchant of <qex>incomparable</qex> wealth.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>A new hypothesis . . . which hath the <qex>incomparable</qex> Sir
Isaac Newton for a patron.</q> <rj><qau>Bp. Warburton.</qau></rj></p>

<p>-- <wordforms><wf>In*com"pa*ra*ble*ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos> --
<wf>In*com"pa*ra*bly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Delights <qex>incomparably</qex> all those corporeal things.</q>
<rj><qau>Bp. Wilkins.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Incompared</ent>⟦br⟧
